BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Bane of the Swarm
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Eris Morn
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: Once a Lightbearer, Eris Morn descended into the Hellmouth of the Moon where she lost her fireteam, her Ghost, and her Light to the Hive.

interactions.flavorLineOne: Eris thanks you for taking part in the celebration. She speaks about the meaning of the Festival and her own experiences with loss, and then hands you a toothbrush.

"A phantom of my deceased fireteam member Sai Mota haunts me. It is only a trick of the Pyramid."

From the Nightmare of Crota, you received an unknown object that harbors a dark energy. You leave it with Eris Morn so she can unearth its secrets.

In the meantime, the Moon hosts further mysteries to uncover regarding entering the Pyramid. The Hive seem to be exhibiting strange behavior that may be related.

Investigate the strange Hive behavior near the Scarlet Keep.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Eris regarding discoveries made within the Black Garden.
headerDisplayProperties.name: The Infection Runs Deep

interactions.flavorLineOne:
The efforts of Guardians within the Black Garden seem to have unlocked the Unknown Artifact. It now provides communications from something sinister. Eris warns us not to bow to it but believes the Artifact too valuable to dispose of.

Collect any further communications it sends, but remain cautious. There is little here to trust.

Somehow, within the Pit of Heresy, the remaining Daughters of Crota managed to revive Zulmak, strengthened and protected by the Darkness within the crystal. With their rejection of sword logic, Crota's daughters have become far more dangerous. You may have scared them off for now, but there is no doubt they will seek revenge.

It is possible you've done a terrible thing in caging such power. But terrible things have forced your hand. Unleash your fury across the system, until all who consider themselves the fever dreams of our eternal torment understand. You, when pushed, are the only nightmare worth fearing.

You have crafted a weapon of corruption and doom, powered by the stolen might of the Hive's wicked Song.

Unleash its fury upon your enemies. Become death.
Eris takes the gift from you, looks at it a moment, and then smiles very faintly. She thanks you and wishes you well.

"This communes with me. And I know it I know him. This is what remains of dear Omar. Tortured by the Hive. I knew not that he would be transformed by Crota's twisted experiments

"I am sorry I couldn't save you, friend. In life, you may have been unable to escape their grasp. But you will have your vengeance yet."

Eris has kept in her possession one of Omar's greatest assets: his beloved Machine Gun. Eris empowers it with the spirit of Omar, and grants it to you.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Eris Morn has heard of your victory over the Undying Mind and wishes to speak to you. Visit her in Sanctuary on the Moon.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Eris Morn

interactions.flavorLineOne: While Eris is pleased that you defeated the Undying Mind, she warns you not to let your guard down. There are greater threats on the horizon. She urges you to keep those threats at the forefront of your mindand prepare accordingly.

"This skull is only the first instrument in our new symphony. With its guidance, we will twist the Hive's tainted lullaby to our will. But first we must bind its gifts. Scour the Moon. Bring me the bones of the damned."

Hunt enemies on the Moon. Gather bones for Eris by completing the activities she requires.

"It is no surprise that the Pyramid now inflicts the phantom of Omar Agah upon me. The Pyramid will do anything to stop us from getting inside."

Hashladn has been disposed of, and with her death comes a path to victory: the Hive Cryptoglyph.

Travel to the Hellmouth and locate the Catacombs within. Hashladn's Cryptoglyph lies inside for the taking.

You have acquired further Nightmare Essences but are out of Hive curios with which to create more Dreambane armor.

After discovering the Hive's ability to shield themselves from the Nightmares, Eris learned of a dark power possessed by the Hive inside the Scarlet Keep. This power may be our answer to how they've protected themselvesand our key to creating more Dreambane armor.

Investigate the dark power within the Scarlet Keep.

The strange Hive rituals within Sorrow's Harbor have proven to be only the tip of the iceberg. Eris believes the remaining Daughters of Crota are sacrificing Nightmares to obtain their dark energy. What the Daughters are using them for, she does not know. But all signs point beneath the Harbor itself.

Search Sorrow's Harbor for the entrance to the Pit of Heresy.

Eris believes that whatever these things are, they want nothing more than to destroy everything we hold dear.

Eris takes the Unknown Artifact from you. She desires to study it in hopes of making sense of all that you saw within the Pyramid.

You now stand at the precipice of the future. The Pyramid holds many secrets within. Lift the veil, and find a way inside. Look for something withinanything that might help humanity fight the oncoming storm.

Return to the Enduring Abyss with a full set of Dreambane armor equipped, and find a way inside the Pyramid.

"The phantom of Eriana-3 now haunts me alongside the rest. They are a burden that weighs heavy on my mind."

The Cryptoglyph must be used to empower the Lectern of Enchantment near Eris. In tandem with the cleansed Essence of Anguish, this will yield another piece of Dreambane armor.

Empower the Lectern of Enchantment with the Cryptoglyph before setting off to hunt the remaining Nightmares.

More Nightmare Essences are required to craft the remaining three pieces of Dreambane armor.

"The Pyramid wastes no timea phantom of Toland has arrived with every intention of distracting me. It will not work."

During Eris's time in the Hellmouth, she discovered many Hive curios. All that remained was an ancient talisman pulsating with Hive magic. Now, the union between the talisman and the Essence of Despair has yielded a powerful tool in the fight against the Nightmares.

Take this piece of Dreambane armor and use it to hunt the Nightmare of Omnigul.

"It appears the screams of Sai's phantom have brought forth another burden for me to bearthe phantom of Vell Tarlowe."

As the Nightmare of Omnigul swept through camp, Eris noticed a strange reaction from the Essence of Despair. Upon further investigation, it appears the Essence can be of use in fighting these Nightmares. But first, it must be cleansed of any dark energy.

Take the Essence of Despair and purify it any way you can. Then, return to Eris Morn.

Eris takes the Void Fizz from you and studies it. "Elemental candies," she says thoughtfully. "A strange way to exploit the power of the Void."

She sets the candy aside and looks at you. "Thank you, Guardian." She pauses."I sometimes wonder if our people rely too much on candy and masks to divert the sting of loss. But then, I'm guilty of my own diversions."

"Of the six of us who descended into the pit, the Hunter Omar Agah surely suffered the most terrible fate. Captured alive by the Heart of Crota, Omar's Light was cut away from him in small bits, used to feed and coax newborn creatures from their cocoons. I will never forget the sounds he made as he died."

Reclaim the true memory of Omar Agah for Eris Morn.

Begin by defeating a powerful Hive Wizard using Super abilities.

"Toland, the mad. Toland, the cursed. The exiled. And finally, the Shattered. He knew more about the Hive and the 'song' of their Deathsingers than any other. Had Eriana-3 questioned his convenient obsession further before recruiting him to our fireteam, things might have been different. But fate is fate. That he could not control."

Reclaim the true memory of Toland for Eris Morn.

Search the Moon's surface for a Hive Trove Guardian obscuring a hidden path.

"Eriana-3 was the Praxic Warlock who led our fireteam of six into the Hellmouth and unknowingly to our doom. I do not blame her, Guardian. During the Great Disaster, Crota snuffed out the love in her heart and left only venom. In the end, before she lost her life in the Oversoul Throne, Eriana-3 came to regret her haste for vengeance."

Reclaim the true memory of Eriana-3 for Eris Morn.

Begin by recovering stolen treasures from Lunar Scavengers beneath the surface of the Moon.

"As ever," Eris says gravely, "I am bidden to grant you dried fruit candies."

She hands you a small box of raisins. "It's traditional at this time of year to trade small gifts and sweets. Perhaps there is someone in this System who would be willing to make a trade for this."

"Sai Mota was a Hunter who walked with us on our doomed journey for vengeance against Crota. Most of us did not make it, however. She fell to the Wizard Omnigul, laughing as she died."

Reclaim the true memory of Sai Mota for Eris Morn.

Begin by searching for the system core vault within the K1 Revelation Lost Sector.

Your success in entering the Pyramid and obtaining the Unknown Artifact has prepared us more than ever for the looming threat of the Darkness. But this is no time for rest.

- Help Eris dispel the phantoms of her lost fireteam

- Hunt Nightmares at higher difficulties

- Uncover the secrets of the Moon's Lost Sectors

- Find further Nightmare Essences spread across the Moon

- Gather Phantasmal Fragments to choose Essences from the Lectern of Enchantment

"Our focus is to be shifted. We created a wake when we destroyed Hashladn and took the Cryptoglyphand that wake has grown and grown. Hashladn's two remaining sisters appear to have picked up where her foul plans left off. Once again, strange Hive rituals have commenced near the Keep. We must tame these plans before they become too grand to handle."

Investigate the Hive rituals in Sorrow's Harbor.

"Vell Tarlowe was one of the strongest Titans I've ever known. A member of the Pilgrim Guard, but even his Light was smothered by the waves of Thrall that rush beneath the surface of the Moon. He underestimated them and he paid the price."

Reclaim the true memory of Vell Tarlowe for Eris Morn.

Begin by completing an active replayable story mission on the Moon.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"We know we should keep ourselves from these deceptive interactions, but what we are learning here are truths previously untold. They are asking to be understood. To be known. Perhaps their intentions are far less black-and-white than we first assumed. As always, stay cautious but perhaps we should not stray from learning the secrets of the universe."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Sinister transmissions seep out from our Unknown Artifact. Their intentions are anything but pure. Place your eyes upon them only if you seek to find truths among the lies."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Somewhere in the space between it all between the truth and the lies, between power and weakness, between day and night, I have lived. In the gray. I believed not by choice, but by force. Chaos reigned, and I embraced it, but ultimately sought to regain equilibrium. Now, however, if these stories are true, I wonder Perhaps there is only chaos. Perhaps it is the only thing worth embracing."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"What first appeared as nonsense and trickery has begun to reveal itself. Certainly we are being manipulated through these interactions, though there is an honesty here a spark of truth that speaks louder than I sought to allow. I will give it some credencebut please, do not let my curiosity infect your truths."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers continue to flow from the Unknown Artifact, but their transmissions have stopped.

Eris, however, has a message for you.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Their transmissions have ceased. But I am confident it is not the end of their trechery. You have continued to stand by me through it all. A beacon of light shining through their forced darkness. For that, I have only this remaining message to give."

Press Accept to receive Eris's message.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Please do not think I have strayed from the Light. Understand that first and foremost, knowledge will save us all. Know thy enemy a clich, yes. But for a reason. Please realize this enemyit is not like our other enemies. It fights with a different kind of force. Were we to simply shoot at it, I fear we would never stand a chance. Sometimes you must accept another's truth to understand their weakness. I hope you'll join me on this journey."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Pay little attention to the false equivalencies within these messages. They seek to use familiarity to lead us into the darker recesses of our minds Do not misunderstandthese are certainly fascinating places to explore. But we do so at the risk of giving ourselves to something without our best interests at heart."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"Perhaps what we think of ourselves is simply within our minds, not in our makeup. Perhaps what built us is not what we thought it was. Always prescribing rationale to the chaos. Always finding light within the dark. Never considering the possibility of a parallel existence within the very building blocks of life. The cards are not what we thought they were. But still we must play the game."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"You must see this The implication is an alteration of the very fabric of reality as we know it. Who or what has life descended from? It cannot be what these transmissions suggest. But at the same time, perhaps maybe I believe you must judge for yourself."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"How long have we lived without questioning the nature of our crafted existence? Do not mistake my curiosity for a turnabout of loyaltythe Light has given us life, while these things have given us only deceit and dysfunction. But perhaps we are not as in control as we'd like to be. After all, what is the point of life without liberty?"

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.

headerDisplayProperties.description:
Whispers flow from the Unknown Artifact, creating sinister messages picked up by Eris Morn.

Someone or something is attempting to speak to us.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Whispers in the Dark

interactions.flavorLineOne:
"These words contain an ancient and unknown power. They are something beyond manipulative ruminations. There is a cry within them, one that seeks to be heard, lost in a sea that only dampens their truths. We must let them be heard. It may be our only way to prepare for whatever comes next."

Press Accept to receive a mysterious transmission.
